Terminalia and Genitalia. Male (
Figs. 12–13
). Ectoprocts oval; gonarcus wide vaulted; parameres close to each other terminal and far separated basal, pelta present; pulvini bursiform, with black setae. Female (
Figs. 15–16
). Ventrovalvae long eggplant shape, without interdens; linguella small; distivalvae nearly oval.
